The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as keypoint (pose) prediction and action classification, which are typically studied in the computer vision subfield of deep learning (cs.CV). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for these tasks also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the method on the PASCAL VOC dataset and comparison to previous approaches indicates a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The introduction of a new dataset for action detection suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of loss functions and evaluation metrics suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
